  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Transfers are often made over cellular as a backup when connection quality is poor.",
    "For larger areas, WiFi might be less practical, showing the advantage of fast cellular connections like 5G.",
    "For automation and for control, e.g., through a video transmission, 5G brings the necessary bandwidth and stability (Agarwala and Guduru 2021).",
    "Also the control of ships or the collection of sensor data from ships will only be possible with fast wireless connections, as stated in the Hamburg 5G trial (Rost et al. 2018).",
    "The use cases described above can be extended to those in terminals where remote crane operations and remote inspections as well as automated trucks can be realized and controlled based on 5G networking (Sun 2021)."
  ],
